MEXICO: Hurricane Dolly forces 29 ports to close in Mexico.Hurricane Dolly forces 29 ports to close in Mexico.Hurricane Dolly forced the closure of 29 Mexican ports, largely just to small vessels, the Communications and Transport Ministry said Tuesday.The ministry said the ports closed included five in Tabasco states, seven in Campeche, 10 in Yucatan and seven in Quintana Roo. It did not name the ports.Earlier Tuesday, Mexico's state-owned oil monopoly Petroleos Mexicanos said none of its crude ports in the south of the country had been affected by Dolly, the fourth big weather front of the Atantic season,--Chris Aspin, Mexico City newsroom (525) 7289530.